{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents colipase (CLPS), a protein that acts as a cofactor required for the activity of pancreatic lipase. CLPS is secreted by the pancreas in an inactive form, procolipase, which is activated in the intestinal lumen by trypsin. Its function is to prevent the inhibitory effect of bile salts on the lipase-catalysed hydrolysis of long-chain triglycerides. Bile salts, at concentrations near their critical micellar concentration, desorb lipase from emulsified triacylglycerol and, thereby, inhibit lipolysis. Colipase functions by anchoring pancreatic lipase to the lipid-water interface through the formation of the stoichiometric colipase-lipase complex [[cite:PUB00004133], [cite:PUB00037363], [cite:PUB00103807], [cite:PUB00103808]]. Members of this protein family are specific to vertebrates.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd23011" "Colipase"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Colipase, chordates", "short" "CLPS_chr"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 6, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 472, "taxa" 1556, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 575, "sets" 0, "proteins" 575, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 442}, "pathways" 12}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR047576", :literature {"PUB00004133" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6391", "authors" ["van Tilbeurgh H" "Sarda L" "Verger R" "Cambillau C."], "ISO_journal" "Nature", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/359159a0", "medline_journal" "Nature", "title" "Structure of the pancreatic lipase-procolipase complex.", "year" 1992, "raw_pages" "159-62", "volume" "359", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 1522902}, "PUB00037363" {"URL" nil, "issue" "3", "authors" ["Breg JN" "Sarda L" "Cozzone PJ" "Rugani N" "Boelens R" "Kaptein R."], "ISO_journal" "Eur. J. Biochem.", "DOI_URL" "h